Anonymous: Oral History Interview by Amy Starecheski

In this interview the interviewee discusses witnessing the legalization process from the perspective of a relative outsider (the interviewee was not a full member of the building until after the process was already underway). The interviewer talks about the unique way that they got access to their apartment and the back-and-forths that happened with the interviewee and other rooms and other buildings. This interview contains a lot of insight about the rules of squatting and how things changed with the legalization of the buildings.
